  "prompt": "I am interested in a girl but she wants to just be friends. What do I do?",
  "response": "Navigating feelings when someone you\u2019re interested in wants to remain friends can be challenging. Here are some steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Respect Her Wishes:** It is crucial to respect her decision. Accept her desire to remain friends and appreciate that she has been honest with you.\n\n2. **Evaluate Your Feelings:** Take some time to understand your feelings. Are you comfortable being just friends, or do you think it will be difficult for you?\n\n3. **Communicate:** If you think it will be hard for you to just be friends due to your feelings, it\u2019s okay to communicate this to her. A respectful conversation about your emotions can be helpful for both of you.\n\n4. **Set Boundaries:** Sometimes taking a step back and setting boundaries can help you manage your feelings better. Limit your contact or take a break to understand what you truly want.\n\n5. **Focus on Other Areas:** Shift your focus to other aspects of your life such as hobbies, interests, and spending time with other friends or family. Keeping yourself engaged in activities you enjoy can be beneficial.\n\n6. **Expand Your Social Circle:** Meeting new people and expanding your social network can help you move forward and provide new perspectives.\n\n7. **Stay Positive:** It\u2019s important to stay positive and be open to the possibility that genuine and fulfilling friendships can evolve into something more over time, but also be okay with the idea that they might not.\n\n8. **Self-Care:** Don\u2019t forget to take care of your emotional well-being. Engage in activities that bring you happiness and help you feel balanced.\n\nAlways remember that building meaningful relationships takes time, and sometimes the best connections come from mutual respect and understanding.",
